      <!-- INTRO -->
      <section id="intro" style="padding: 0; margin-bottom: 3rem;">
        <p>
          Entering the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia was historically one of the most challenging travel logistics in the world, restricted primarily to religious pilgrims, business invitees, and sponsored expatriate workers. However, as a core pillar of the **Saudi Vision 2030** transformation program, the country has opened its borders to global tourism. The launching of the unified tourist visa platform has revolutionized entry procedures, simplifying a once-complex process into a fast, transparent, and highly accessible system. Today, millions of international travelers can secure entry authorization online within minutes, making the Kingdom a leading destination for leisure, adventure, and spiritual journeys.
        </p>
        <p>
          The unified platform administered by the **Ministry of Tourism** and the **General Directorate of Passports (Jawazat)** coordinates the various entry categories. This streamlined approach ensures that whether you are arriving at King Khalid International Airport (RUH) in Riyadh or King Abdulaziz International Airport (JED) in Jeddah, your border clearance is fast and digital. In 2026, the country has further expanded its eligible nationalities list, updated its on-arrival regulations, and integrated its transit visa schemes with national carriers like Saudia and flyadeal, creating a highly cohesive travel ecosystem.
        </p>
        <p>
          This guide provides an exhaustive, authoritative breakdown of all Saudi visa types, detailing costs, validity periods, processing times, and eligibility criteria. By understanding the specific requirements for your nationality and travel purpose, you can prevent border delays and plan a seamless journey to the historic sites of AlUla, the vibrant stadiums of FIFA 2034, or the sacred precincts of Makkah and Madinah.
        </p>

        <!-- QUICK FACTS TABLE -->
