      <section id="faqs" style="padding: 0; margin-bottom: 3rem;">
        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        
        <div class="faq-item">
          <strong>Can I perform Umrah on a tourist visa?</strong>
          <p>
            Yes, the standard Saudi Tourist eVisa allows you to perform the minor pilgrimage (Umrah) at any time of the year, except during the official Hajj season dates. You must download the official **Nusuk App** on your smartphone to register your visa details and book a permit slot to perform Umrah or pray in the sacred *Rawdah* at the Prophet's Mosque in Madinah.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <strong>Is travel insurance mandatory for Saudi Arabia?</strong>
          <p>
            Yes. Travel health insurance is mandatory for all visitors entering Saudi Arabia on a tourist visa. If you apply for an eVisa, the cost of this insurance (180 SAR) is automatically included in the total fee of 480 SAR, and your insurance policy is issued instantly from an approved local Saudi provider. If you are entering on a different visa type, you must secure valid travel health insurance that covers emergency medical care within the Kingdom.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <strong>How long does the Saudi eVisa take to process?</strong>
          <p>
            Most Saudi eVisas are processed and approved within 5 to 24 hours of submission. In many cases, applicants receive their digital visa PDF in their email inbox within 10 minutes. However, to account for potential processing delays or system maintenance, it is highly recommended to submit your eVisa application at least **3 to 5 days** before your scheduled flight.
          </p>
        </div>
